explanation: Binary search the minimal possible stability factor. For each candidate length L, check if every window of length L can be made stable with ≤ maxC changes by testing small divisors (≤100). The sliding-window DP counts minimal changes per divisor; if any divisor works for any window, the length L can be eliminated.

